category = "Basic syntax"
title = "Variables"
content = "You can declare variables using the [code]var[/code] keyword. You have to specify its type after the variable name using a colon and the type of the variables.

[code]var my_int: int[/code]

After declaring a variable, you can assign it a value using [code]=[/code]:

[code]my_var = 42[/code]

You can assign variables to other declared, assigned variables:
[code]
var my_var1: int
var my_var2: int
my_var1 = 6
my_var2 = my_var1
[/code]
Or you can use expressions to calculate something and assign it to the variable:
[code]
my_var2 = 7*my_var1
print(my_var2)
[/code]
This should print [code]42[/code]!"
